</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F19FF8EFF26FBDBFC8EFB7A" blockId="44.[151,1437,613,1288]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
Habitat. Infralittoral species, 
<quantity id="2E379B383F19FF8EFDF2FBDBFDBBFB99" box="[531,603,1117,1144]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" unit="m" value="1.0" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="0.0">0–2 m</quantity>
depth on rocky shores, in clefts, below stones, hidden in biocover, in the Black Sea also in brackish waters (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F19FF8EFDFCFB07FD5EFB7A" author="Kovacic, M." box="[541,702,1153,1179]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="423 - 435" refId="ref57644" refString="Kovacic, M. (1997) Cryptobenthic gobies and clingfishes in the Kvarner area, Adriatic Sea. Natura Croatica, 6 (4), 423 - 435." type="journal article" year="1997">Kovačić 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F19FF8EFD2BFB04FC81FB7A" author="Patzner, R. A." box="[714,865,1153,1180]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" refId="ref62855" refString="Patzner, R. A. (2021) Gobiidae. Available from: http: // www. patzner. sbg. ac. at / Gobiidae / GobiidaeSpecies. htm (accessed 1 October 2021)" type="url" year="2021">Patzner 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F19FF8EFF26FB23FD3EFAE9" blockId="44.[151,1437,613,1288]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
